## Closed-World Assumption

Under the Closed-World Assumption: any property not explicitly asserted for an entity in the
witness domain is **False**. For "either A or B" patterns, model as exclusive (exactly one is
true): use `truth["A(e)"] != truth["B(e)"]`. Do not assume unmentioned relationships hold.

